    {
      "id": "d3ae2229bb07b158ac12216c2df07f7da6251a7b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-06 21:34:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nHmm, it seems we have both \"struct ldlm_callback_suite\" and \"struct ldlm_enqueue_info\".  I think it makes more sense to merge these two structures, so that ldlm_enqueue_info has proper function pointer declarations for the callbacks, but we use a single \"callback argument\" structure in the LDLM code.  The ldlm_enqueue_info also includes the lock type and flags, which are common to all of the places where ldlm_callback_suite is also being used.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "18c9ddc47fed1c1c8ff63484a84e878e70b4db4d",
