      "date": "2013-05-08 16:13:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(9 inline comments)\n\nThere is a bit of trailing whitespace in the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "823d4011b358e5afba9aa4983c04256f7fc9d973",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-08 19:02:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(72 inline comments)\n\nQuite a large number of coding style issues that would have been caught earlier if the checkpatch.pl output in the commit message was looked at.  Please ensure you have the right commit hooks installed:\n\n ln -sf ../../build/commit-msg .git/hooks/\n ln -sf ../../build/prepare-commit-msg .git/hooks/\n\nIn any case, there is also a potential defect in the patch, because it is passing the address of a structure on the stack back to the calling function, and my reading shows that \"const\" is not enough to ensure that the structure is allocated in global memory.  It needs to be declared as \"static\" for that to happen.\n\nThis, in turn, opens up a large optimization in ldlm_lock memory reduction, because the static ldlm_callback_suite structures can be shared among all locks of that type, instead of copied separately into every one of the millions of locks in memory.\n\nOne other minor change is that it would be nicer if \"cbs\" were named \"lcs\" everywhere, so that it matches the structure field prefixes.  I don't think it is an improvement to have two different common names for these structures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
