        "subject": "LU-3276 ldlm: reduce a stack usage in ldlm lock enq",
        "message": "LU-3276 ldlm: reduce a stack usage in ldlm lock enq\n\nwe don't need a pass a callbacks as separate parameters,\nas it's converted into ldlm_callback_suite, we may create\nldlm_callback_suite on top of call and make it's const\nto reduce stack usage (56 vs 88 bytes).\n\nSigned-off-by: Alexey Lyashkov <alexey_lyashkov@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I16da3da2d2902427c0321e0806e5a1ad68d18857\n"
